# Environment Variables for Netlify Deployment

## Required Database Variables
DB_HOST=your-database-host.com
DB_PORT=5432
DB_NAME=your_database_name
DB_USER=your_database_user
DB_PASSWORD=your_secure_password

## JWT Secret (CHANGE THIS!)
JWT_SECRET=your_super_secret_jwt_key_here_please_change_in_production

## Application Settings
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=3000

## CORS Settings (Optional)
FRONTEND_URL=https://your-frontend-domain.com

## Database Recommendations for Netlify:

# Supabase (Free PostgreSQL + Auth)
# - Go to https://supabase.com
# - Create new project
# - Use connection details from Settings > Database

# Neon (Serverless PostgreSQL)
# - Go to https://neon.tech
# - Create new project
# - Use connection string provided

# ElephantSQL (Free PostgreSQL)
# - Go to https://www.elephantsql.com
# - Create new instance
# - Use connection details provided

## How to set these in Netlify:
# 1. Go to your Netlify site dashboard
# 2. Go to Site Settings > Environment Variables
# 3. Add each variable one by one
# 4. Deploy your site
